narratives.question_text: Were the resources provided to you by the School and University adequate for the fulfillment of the work assigned?  If not, please make suggestions.
comments: Instructor: Alan Organschi  I think the resources were adequate.
Instructor: Alan Organschi  yes, except for the constant problems with plotters and printing students encounters in this school.
Instructor: Jennifer Wei Leung  Resources were adequate.
Instructor: Jennifer Wei Leung  The resources were available.
Instructor: Jennifer Wei Leung  The resources provided were adequate.
Instructor: Joel Sanders  More than sufficient, though a model building budget for some of the projects would be nice.
Instructor: Joel Sanders  Yes, everything was fine.

Instructor: Joseph Moore  It would be better if we had section ta's that were actually involved with our production. Last semester I saw my ta twice and am seriously questioning the pedagogical intent of the school. I'm surprised we had ta listed as I cannot recall seeing him in our studio more than once and maybe receiving three emails from his throughout the semester. What is the point of having a ta if they are barely involved in our education and never in studio?
Instructor: Joseph Moore  The resources provided were fine, though common tables in studio would have been nice so that BP teams could meet more effectively.
Instructor: Joseph Moore  Yes, all the resources were adequate.
Instructor: Joseph Moore  Budgets should have been available for each team in the building project.
